  "texts": [
    "In the following, we briefly describe them and their application to the considered CV tasks (Fig. 3).",
    "CycleGANs are made up of two generators that learn two mapping functions from an image domain X to a different image domain Y and vice versa, and two discriminators D X and D Y aimed at distinguishing between real and generated images.",
    "CycleGANs have been used for Re-Id to improve accuracy under low light conditions (e.g., at night time) through the use of thermal infrared images by Zheng et al. (2021).",
    "Due to the limited number of thermal infrared data sets, a CycleGAN model was trained to translate RGB images into thermal ones.",
    "The trained GAN was then used to generate thermal images of data sets which do not contain this kind of data."
  ],
